  "response_text": "In concrete canyons, steel and stone,\nA sea of faces, yet I am alone,\nLost in the crowd, a solitary soul,\nA stranger in a world that's lost its goal.\n\nThe city pulses, a vibrant beat,\nA symphony of sounds, a kaleidoscope of feet,\nBut amidst the noise, I feel a void,\nA chasm deep, where love and connection should reside.\n\nI search for eyes that meet my own,\nA smile, a glance, a friendly tone,\nBut in this sea of strangers, I'm adrift,\nA leaf on a river, without a rift.\n\nThe city's energy, a double-edged sword,\nIt brings me life, yet leaves me scarred,\nA paradox of connection and disconnection,\nA world that's full, yet feels like a desolation.\n\nI wander streets, a ghost in the night,\nA fleeting thought, a moment's light,\nI try to find my place, my tribe,\nBut in this crowd",
